President Obama announced his intent to nominate Matthew C. Armstrong for the position of Member of the Broadcasting Board of Governors. Armstrong is an author, speaker, and strategist specializing in public diplomacy. He previously served as Executive Director of the U.S. Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy and as an adjunct professor at the Annenberg School of Journalism and Communication. Armstrong also founded the MountainRunner Institute and has published a blog on public diplomacy and strategic communication. He holds a B.A. and an M.P.D. from the University of Southern California.